{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And immediately when I found out to a [? lageralteste, ?] I made contact with him, and I helped him a lot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and-- and we had sometimes even meetings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was strictly forbidden.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If the Nazis would have known that, that is-- if three people chat together and talked, that was considered conspiracy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and-- the answer for conspiracy was death.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the punishment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and-- and we even had a Hanukkah party.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On-- in-- in-- in December of '43, we made the first time Hanukkah party in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and-- and I remember [INAUDIBLE] is their leader.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] is their-- their-- of the group that was instructing them all the time, like they have a counselor in-- in a camps, you know-- in-- in-- in youth camps.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember-- I would never forget this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He compared what we're going through with the situation in Israel when the Maccabees came into power, where the [INAUDIBLE] took over, the Romans took over, and everything was forbidden.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they forced them to-- to-- to [? prophetize ?] and they forced him to-- to-- to bring foreign gods into-- into-- into-- into a temple and what have you, and still, to survive, and they won in the end.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that will be with us too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We have to be strong.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We have to never lose our optimism, never lose our will to survive, and eventually, liberation would come.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And-- and then we would sing a Hebrew song.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was so dangerous, but we had guards outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Even as [INAUDIBLE] guard forbids comes in, we got to-- immediately we have to disperse.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
